    "headline": "Google top India counsel quits in latest departure amid regulatory hurdles, sources say",
    "summary": "Google's top India counsel, Bijoya Roy, has resigned after ‌16 months in the role, two sources ‌said, a high-profile exit in a key market where the U.S. ​tech giant is facing regulatory hurdles and also lacks a government relations head.  India is crucial for Alphabet's Google since most smartphones in the country run on its Android ‌operating system, even ⁠as Apple's share is growing steadily.  Google also faces antitrust cases in India, legal challenges ⁠over AI training and stricter-than-ever content takedown regulations that started applying to tech companies from February.",
